    5. Cannot find candidates who combine operational coordination skills with hands-on AI/ML technical depth
    6. BFSI client architectures require extensive compliance/security rework post-delivery

  B. Strategic Needs:
    1. Capture BFSI GenAI market opportunity before competitors by streamlining POC-to-production pipeline
    2. Secure AWS Advanced or Premier partner tier through competency achievements to win enterprise deals
    3. Reduce project delivery costs through reusable infrastructure patterns and faster POC cycles
    4. Enable cloud department to scale from current size to support 3-5x client growth without proportional hiring

  C. Risks if Unfilled:
    1. Lost revenue from failed AWS funding applications forcing clients to postpone or cancel POCs
    2. Delivery delays causing client churn in competitive BFSI GenAI market
    3. AWS partner tier downgrade eliminating co-sell opportunities and funding access
    4. Engineering team burnout from covering both operational chaos AND technical delivery
    5. Compliance violations or security incidents from rushed BFSI deployments

